@NODE 1. "Introduction to V1.1"

 Welcome to the Diamond Caves Leveleditor V1.1

 This program provides an easy and comfortable way to create and design
 your own Levels for Diamond Caves V1.x.

 This program is based on MUI, see @{"About MUI" Link 8.}.

 To change the screenmode and some default-settings you should use the
 program "DiamondPrefs", if you want to reconfigure the outfit, use
 "MUI-Prefs".

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "Requirements"

 The Diamond Caves Editor requires:

 - Kick 2.0
 - 1 MB chipmem
 - MUI 2.3
 - a registered version of Diamond Caves
 - Commodore's Installer (can be found on your Workbench-Install-Disk)

 recommended:

 - Kick3.x
 - 68020 (or higher)
 - 2 MB chipmem

@ENDNODE

@NODE 3. "Installation"

 The Diamond Caves Editor comes with a ready-to-run installer-script for
 the Commodore Installer. Just click on the icon and follow the text in the
 window.

 Basically, the script will copy all necessary files in the Directory "DC:"
 according to the present version.

@ENDNODE

