@NODE 9. "Import Levels"

 Since V1.1 the Diamond Caves Editor is able to load and convert Levels
 from other Boulder Dash clones.

 You have to select the type of Level you want to load:

 Balder's Grove: These Levels are loaded including the extra steel border
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ around the playfield because Balder's Grove supports Exits
 in the border. Note: The "Snake" in Balder's Grove leaves 9 Emeralds
 behind, the "Bug" in Diamond Caves 8 Emeralds and 1 Diamonds. You may have
 to increase the number of Emeralds to collect to match the new value.

 Emerald Mine: This type includes Levels from Emerald Mine I, II and III.
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~ The only thing Diamond Caves does not support is Dynamite
 that's already lit. This item will be replaced by a question mark. You can
 easy simulate a burning Dynamite with a falling Bomb.

 Emerald Mine CD: I'm not sure if I've got the Leveldescription 100% right,
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ so if you encounter any problems (e.g. questionsmarks in
 the playfield), please contact me.

 If you want another Boulder Dash clone to be supported by the Diamond
 Caves Editor, feel free to contact me.

@ENDNODE
